armpit of a town just as much as you.

998
01:08:58.534 --> 01:09:00.695
And last time I checked.

999
01:09:00.803 --> 01:09:03.795
getting arrested is not
the kind of extracurricular

1000
01:09:03.873 --> 01:09:06.603
that Ivy League schools
are looking for.

1001
01:09:07.310 --> 01:09:11.974
Do you really think that this roller
derby career of yours is going anywhere?

1002
01:09:13.282 --> 01:09:14.306
That's not what
it's about.

1003
01:09:14.384 --> 01:09:16.045
Oh. yeah. right.

1004
01:09:16.152 --> 01:09:17.710
I'm sorry. Pash.

1005
01:09:26.696 --> 01:09:28.527
Thanks for
letting me stay.

1006
01:09:28.631 --> 01:09:29.723
Anytime.

1007
01:09:32.568 --> 01:09:35.662
That's Riley back there.
He's my little man.

1008
01:09:38.675 --> 01:09:40.870
So that's why you never
come out with us?

1009
01:09:40.977 --> 01:09:43.673
Yeah. he pretty much owns
my ass. Don't you. Rile?

1010
01:09:45.815 --> 01:09:49.251
Okay. first stop. sitter.
Then the Warehouse.

1011
01:09:59.929 --> 01:10:03.194
Ruthless. Ruthless.
Ruthless.

1012
01:10:05.101 --> 01:10:06.898
Maven. Maven. Maven?

1013
01:10:08.671 --> 01:10:10.605
Hey. guess how old I am.

1014
01:10:12.675 --> 01:10:13.869
Twenty-seven?

1015
01:10:13.943 --> 01:10:15.274
Oh. that's sweet.

1016
01:10:16.946 --> 01:10:19.244
I'm 36

1017
01:10:21.184 --> 01:10:23.379
Guess when I
started skating.

1018
01:10:24.020 --> 01:10:25.453
I was 31.

1019
01:10:26.556 --> 01:10:32.722
'Cause it took me that long to find
one thing that I was really good at.

1020
01:10:36.099 --> 01:10:40.559
And you know what? I
worked my ass off to get it.

1021
01:10:42.739 --> 01:10:44.206
Yeah. me. too.

1022
01:10:45.608 --> 01:10:47.803
It's too bad
you're only 17.

1023
01:10:49.946 --> 01:10:53.575
What do you think the league is
gonna say when they find that out?

1024
01:10:53.649 --> 01:10:57.415
Or your teammates. when they
find out you've been lying?

1025
01:10:57.487 --> 01:10:59.819
That's gonna be rough.
Maven. please. Look...

1026
01:10:59.922 --> 01:11:01.389
No. you look.

1027
01:11:01.457 --> 01:11:04.949
One day it will be your time.
Ruthless. but it's not your time now.

1028
01:11:05.061 --> 01:11:08.997
And if I was you. I wouldn't even
bother lacing up those skates.

1029
01:11:30.019 --> 01:11:31.111
Fuck.

1030
01:11:33.656 --> 01:11:36.454
It's Oliver. I'm running
with the bulls right now.

1031
01:11:37.660 --> 01:11:39.025
Hey. Oliver.

1032
01:11:41.197 --> 01:11:45.190
I just need to talk to you. I...
I'm calling you from a payphone.

1033
01:11:48.304 --> 01:11:50.101
Look. I've left home.

1034
01:11:53.643 --> 01:11:57.636
I... You know. this...
I don't...

1035
01:11:57.713 --> 01:12:00.011
I don't wanna do this
on voicemail.

1036
01:12:00.116 --> 01:12:03.813
so maybe you can get me
on Maggie's phone.

1037
01:12:04.887 --> 01:12:08.846
512-697-4998

1038
01:12:10.326 --> 01:12:14.387
And then we can just... We
can talk later. Okay. bye.

1039
01:12:18.301 --> 01:12:19.996
- Oink Joint
- Hey. B.

1040
01:12:20.403 --> 01:12:21.563
Hey. Bliss.

1041
01:12:21.671 --> 01:12:22.831
Is Pash there?

1042
01:12:25.141 --> 01:12:26.665
She's not here.

1043
01:12:30.913 --> 01:12:32.505
Yeah. okay.
Bye.

1044
01:12:44.327 --> 01:12:49.492
If. you know. you hear a
hint of pain in my voice

1045
01:12:49.565 --> 01:12:52.261
when I say that I've
lost my best friend..

1046
01:12:52.368 --> 01:12:55.826
.. to a gang of
roller skating she-males

1047
01:12:56.439 --> 01:12:59.704
and that the only highlight of my
night was serving corn to an old man

1048
01:12:59.775 --> 01:13:03.711
who can't even chew it.
then I'd say you're wrong.

1049
01:13:06.515 --> 01:13:07.846
I'm happy.

1050
01:13:24.233 --> 01:13:27.532
Okay. that was odd.

1051
01:13:32.041 --> 01:13:33.565
Oddly glorious.

1052
01:13:35.244 --> 01:13:37.109
Ruthless. what's up?

1053
01:13:38.748 --> 01:13:41.979
I just had something
I wanted to tell you all.

1054
01:13:42.418 --> 01:13:44.283
Seventeen!?

1055
01:13:44.387 --> 01:13:45.581
What if you'd
gotten hurt?

1056
01:13:45.655 --> 01:13:47.748
Her parents could sue
the league. you guys.

1057
01:13:47.823 --> 01:13:48.812
I know.

1058
01:13:48.925 --> 01:13:50.790
We're in enough trouble with
the fire marshal as it is.

1059
01:13:50.927 --> 01:13:52.554
- Exactly.
- You know what? She can still play..

1060
01:13:52.662 --> 01:13:56.120
.. as long as she gets permission
from one of her parents.

1061
01:13:58.267 --> 01:13:59.495
I can't.

1062
01:13:59.769 --> 01:14:02.932
I'm not even living
at home right now.

1063
01:14:03.005 --> 01:14:07.465
Well. even though you can't skate
with us. and you're a big liar.

1064
01:14:07.576 --> 01:14:09.601
You're still
a Hurl Scout.

1065
01:14:09.812 --> 01:14:12.007
Yeah. you could
be our mascot.

1066
01:14:17.586 --> 01:14:21.317
You can't understand until you
have one. everything changes.

1067
01:14:23.526 --> 01:14:26.120
Yeah. that's what
my mom always says.

1068
01:14:26.529 --> 01:14:28.360
But you're not
really like her. though.

1069
01:14:28.497 --> 01:14:29.794
Oh. I'm the cool aunt?

1070
01:14:29.865 --> 01:14:30.991
Yeah.

1071
01:14:34.537 --> 01:14:38.337
Why don't I just cut school and
hang out with you guys today?

1072
01:14:39.675 --> 01:14:41.336
Bliss. I know what it's like
to wanna do your own thing.

1073
01:14:41.444 --> 01:14:42.536
believe me. I do.

1074
01:14:42.645 --> 01:14:45.273
But maybe there's
a way you can do it

1075
01:14:45.348 --> 01:14:48.181
without making your
parents feel like crap?

1076
01:14:49.218 --> 01:14:51.152
What?
I've just been thinking.

1077
01:14:51.220 --> 01:14:54.883
I think maybe you're being a
little selfish with your mom.

1078
01:14:59.729 --> 01:15:01.060
Okay. no.

1079
01:15:02.732 --> 01:15:05.496
She's the one who has
been shoving her agenda

1080
01:15:05.568 --> 01:15:07.798
down my throat
since day one.

1081
01:15:08.971 --> 01:15:12.463
First of all. you're lucky
to have a mom that even cares.

1082
01:15:12.541 --> 01:15:14.338
And just because
she's wrong about derby.

1083
01:15:14.410 --> 01:15:17.709
doesn't mean she's wrong
about every single thing.

1084
01:15:17.813 --> 01:15:21.010
And if Riley ever lies to me
the way you lied to your parents.

1085
01:15:21.083 --> 01:15:23.551
He wouldn't even be able to run
away 'cause I'd break his legs.

1086
01:15:24.920 --> 01:15:27.650
I'm just kidding. honey.
That was a joke.

1087
01:15:30.393 --> 01:15:31.860
I am here for you.

1088
01:15:31.927 --> 01:15:36.921
but just because you've found a new family
doesn't mean you throw the old one away.

1089
01:15:48.444 --> 01:15:51.106
Have a swell day at
school. sweetheart.

1090
01:15:53.616 --> 01:15:54.913
You didn't see that.
did you?

1091
01:17:14.029 --> 01:17:16.361
Please don't
judge me right now.

1092
01:17:23.272 --> 01:17:28.107
Whoever he is.
He doesn't deserve you.

1093
01:17:30.713 --> 01:17:32.044
Come here.

1094
01:17:36.719 --> 01:17:38.118
I feel sick.

1095
01:17:39.488 --> 01:17:40.978
I know you do.

1096
01:17:51.233 --> 01:17:53.133
I gave him everything.

1097
01:17:53.669 --> 01:17:56.570
No. don't say that.

1098
01:18:05.414 --> 01:18:06.904
No. it's true.

1099
01:18:09.585 --> 01:18:10.745
I did.

1100
01:18:40.115 --> 01:18:42.106
That's a lot to process.

1101
01:18:48.457 --> 01:18:50.948
She was wearing
my Stryper T-shirt.

1102
01:18:51.894 --> 01:18:54.124
I just don't understand
how he could do that.

1103
01:18:54.230 --> 01:18:55.697
Your T-shirt?

1104
01:18:57.533 --> 01:18:59.933
It's the only
cool thing you own.

1105
01:19:00.202 --> 01:19:01.794
That you'd know about.

1106
01:19:03.105 --> 01:19:04.470
Stryper.

1107
01:19:10.412 --> 01:19:12.607
Mom. this isn't...

1108
01:19:13.415 --> 01:19:15.883
This isn't working.

1109
01:19:17.753 --> 01:19:18.947
I know.

1110
01:19:20.122 --> 01:19:22.454
You just make me
feel so guilty.

1111
01:19:23.826 --> 01:19:27.387
That's not what I want.

1112
01:19:29.398 --> 01:19:31.298
I deserve it sometimes.

1113
01:19:31.834 --> 01:19:37.932
Well. I know I can go
overboard sometimes.

1114
01:19:39.908 --> 01:19:43.400
But when the person that
you love more than anything

1115
01:19:43.479 --> 01:19:46.346
tells you
that you suck. it...

1116
01:19:49.285 --> 01:19:52.948
If you want me to do the Miss
Blue Bonnet pageant. I will.

1117
01:19:53.022 --> 01:19:56.082
No. no. no. no.
We're way past that.

1118
01:19:56.158 --> 01:19:59.787
No. it's not a big deal. I
mean. we already got the dress.

1119
01:20:04.700 --> 01:20:06.964
Don't do it for me.

1120
01:20:08.170 --> 01:20:10.331
Fine. I'll do it
for myself.

1121
01:20:17.813 --> 01:20:19.644
Look who's back.

1122
01:20:20.649 --> 01:20:21.707
Hi.

1123
01:20:29.224 --> 01:20:30.851
Glad you're safe.

1124
01:20:33.329 --> 01:20:35.559
I shouldn't have said
those things to you.

1125
01:20:40.035 --> 01:20:42.060
Already forgotten. kiddo.

1126
01:20:52.014 --> 01:20:54.812
She's trying to
look pathetic on purpose.

1127
01:20:58.987 --> 01:21:01.751
How long you gonna
hold onto that grudge?

1128
01:21:12.101 --> 01:21:13.329
Thanks.

1129
01:21:16.572 --> 01:21:19.097
Pash. I'm sorry.
You see. I just...

1130
01:21:19.208 --> 01:21:20.698
Come on.

1131
01:21:20.776 --> 01:21:22.107
I'm sorry.

1132
01:21:25.114 --> 01:21:26.775
I'm really sorry.

1133
01:21:27.950 --> 01:21:29.178
I know.

1134
01:21:31.053 --> 01:21:33.453
Just keep...
Keep saying it.

1135
01:21:33.555 --> 01:21:34.579
Yeah.

1136
01:21:34.690 --> 01:21:36.055
Over and over
again. please.

1137
01:21:36.125 --> 01:21:38.286
Yeah. I will.
I'll keep it up.

1138
01:21:40.129 --> 01:21:41.255
So what happened?

1139
01:21:41.363 --> 01:21:44.799
God. I just feel
like such...

1140
01:21:45.300 --> 01:21:50.533
I'm stupid. I'm just... I feel
so stupid for falling for it.

1141
01:21:51.407 --> 01:21:54.399
Yeah. that's why I like
a good fondling. you know?

1142
01:21:54.476 --> 01:21:56.273
It's so much simpler.

1143
01:21:57.379 --> 01:22:02.146
Well. while you were
off gallivanting. I...

1144
01:22:03.652 --> 01:22:05.313
I got some news.

1145
01:22:07.089 --> 01:22:08.886
What... What... What's...

1146
01:22:09.324 --> 01:22:11.315
I got into some colleges.

1147
01:22:12.828 --> 01:22:13.920
Wow!

1148
01:22:13.996 --> 01:22:16.226
My parents want me
to go to Johns Hopkins.

1149
01:22:16.298 --> 01:22:20.632
but I think I'm
gonna go to Columbia.

1150
01:22:20.736 --> 01:22:24.797
I know. I'm gonna see what it's like
to live in New York for a little while.

1151
01:22:24.907 --> 01:22:26.841
That's amazing.

1152
01:22:33.282 --> 01:22:35.773
Do you still have
his stupid jacket?

1153
01:22:44.993 --> 01:22:47.154
Did he turn into
a handsome prince?

1154
01:22:47.262 --> 01:22:48.854
No. he stayed a Birdman.

1155
01:22:49.531 --> 01:22:52.989
But the worst part is.
he's actually a good kisser.

1156
01:22:54.369 --> 01:22:55.927
Really good.

1157
01:22:56.038 --> 01:22:58.131
Congratulations
are in order.

1158
01:22:58.207 --> 01:23:00.937
Uh. no. Let's not
encourage this.

1159
01:23:02.044 --> 01:23:04.171
I like Birdman.
He's nice.

1160
01:23:04.279 --> 01:23:07.976
Hey. Bliss. somebody on the
phone for you. A Maggie Mayhem?

1161
01:23:09.184 --> 01:23:10.208
Well. look at you.

1162
01:23:10.319 --> 01:23:11.308
I got a makeover.

1163
01:23:11.386 --> 01:23:12.876
Yes. you did.

1164
01:23:18.060 --> 01:23:19.220
Hello.

1165
01:23:19.328 --> 01:23:20.659
Ruthless.
it's the championship.

1166
01:23:20.729 --> 01:23:23.129
Don't even tell me
you can't make it.

1167
01:23:23.198 --> 01:23:24.222
I can't.

1168
01:23:24.833 --> 01:23:28.234
Is it her mom? Let me talk
to her. I'll knock her out.

1169
01:23:29.204 --> 01:23:31.069
Just tell your mom
it's important.

1170
01:23:32.040 --> 01:23:34.804
The pageant is the same day
as the game. and I can't.

1171
01:23:34.877 --> 01:23:38.142
Well. you have to try harder and
you have to make it work. We need you.

1172
01:23:38.247 --> 01:23:39.680
- Let me talk to her mom.
- Bye.

1173
01:23:39.748 --> 01:23:41.682
I'll kick her in her...

1174
01:23:42.818 --> 01:23:44.547
You're selling out.

1175
01:24:00.669 --> 01:24:02.261
"Babe Ruthless."

1176
01:24:03.338 --> 01:24:05.533
A classic
move in derby.

1177
01:24:05.607 --> 01:24:08.667
Babe and Maggie go for the
whip. and it's effective.

1178
01:24:08.744 --> 01:24:13.238
Nothing gives you speed like
a whip. Look at Ruthless fly.

1179
01:24:22.891 --> 01:24:24.552
Excuse me. ladies.

1180
01:24:25.193 --> 01:24:28.629
I'm looking for Maggie.
Maggie Mayhem.

1181
01:24:33.468 --> 01:24:35.265
Good pageant. y'all.

1182
01:24:38.807 --> 01:24:40.604
Love the dress. Amber.

1183
01:24:44.880 --> 01:24:47.474
- We'll have to break through.
- I know.

1184
01:24:47.649 --> 01:24:48.980
What time is it?

1185
01:24:51.653 --> 01:24:54.417
- Your gown is custom. huh?
- Yeah.

1186
01:24:54.489 --> 01:24:56.753
It's beautiful.

1187
01:24:56.825 --> 01:24:58.122
Thanks.

1188
01:24:59.995 --> 01:25:02.225
Your dress is nice
too Amber.

1189
01:25:04.333 --> 01:25:05.664
- Hey.
- Hey.

1190
01:25:07.469 --> 01:25:09.061
We need to talk.

1191
01:25:14.576 --> 01:25:16.601
Ma'am. put down
the lip gloss.

1192
01:25:16.678 --> 01:25:18.111
Step away from the mirror.

1193
01:25:20.482 --> 01:25:23.178
What are you all doing
here? Are you...

1194
01:25:23.585 --> 01:25:25.109
You're just springing
this on me now?

1195
01:25:25.187 --> 01:25:26.677
I know the timing sucks.

1196
01:25:26.788 --> 01:25:28.949
but I've been thinking. You
know. I'm not so bothered

1197
01:25:29.024 --> 01:25:30.992
by her playing
this roller derby.

1198
01:25:31.093 --> 01:25:32.583
In fact. I think
it's kind of neat.

1199
01:25:32.661 --> 01:25:35.596
I went on the website. they got
Blisster's pictures all over.

1200
01:25:35.664 --> 01:25:37.461
And it looks like they're
having a ton of fun.

1201
01:25:37.532 --> 01:25:41.866
Earl. we just spent a lot of
money on a custom-made gown.

1202
01:25:41.970 --> 01:25:44.461
And you want her
to just up and quit?

1203
01:25:44.539 --> 01:25:46.973
Yeah. but her team is in
the league championships.

1204
01:25:47.042 --> 01:25:48.805
The game's tonight.

1205
01:25:48.877 --> 01:25:52.313
$800. Earl.

1206
01:25:55.317 --> 01:25:57.478
I can take
losing the money.

1207
01:25:58.387 --> 01:26:02.380
I cannot take losing the
chance for our kid to be happy.

1208
01:26:04.526 --> 01:26:06.687
- I love her.
- Yeah. she looks nice

1209
01:26:06.795 --> 01:26:08.228
- Really sweet.
- Bliss.

1210
01:26:08.330 --> 01:26:09.627
You guys gotta
hide. my mom's coming.

1211
01:26:09.731 --> 01:26:12.564
- Bliss.
- Seriously you guys have to hide.

1212
01:26:14.836 --> 01:26:15.996
Bliss.

1213
01:26:16.338 --> 01:26:19.501
Your daddy is about to come in here
and tell you that he thinks it's okay

1214
01:26:19.574 --> 01:26:22.873
for you to go off
and play roller derby.

1215
01:26:23.311 --> 01:26:25.040
- I don't agree.
- Mom.

1216
01:26:25.147 --> 01:26:30.016
When you told me that you weren't
doing the Miss Blue Bonnet for me.

1217
01:26:30.519 --> 01:26:32.316
did you mean it?

1218
01:26:42.097 --> 01:26:45.589
Well. good luck.

1219
01:27:03.719 --> 01:27:07.746
Come on. ladies.
What are we waiting for?

1220
01:27:07.856 --> 01:27:08.845
Ready to play!

1221
01:27:09.791 --> 01:27:11.053
Okay!

1222
01:27:15.130 --> 01:27:16.430
Wait.

1223
01:27:18.725 --> 01:27:20.090
One more thing.

1224
01:27:21.136 --> 01:27:24.230
- Yeah. come on. let's go!
- Good luck. Amber!

1225
01:27:24.306 --> 01:27:25.534
Step it up!

1226
01:27:31.713 --> 01:27:33.943
That's when...

1227
01:27:34.049 --> 01:27:35.141
Hi.

1228
01:27:38.587 --> 01:27:39.918
I got it.

1229
01:27:40.822 --> 01:27:43.484
We just got back into town.
I came straight over.

1230
01:27:43.592 --> 01:27:47.756
I probably still smell
like the van. But...

1231
01:27:48.230 --> 01:27:51.757
I went on your website and saw some
girl wearing my Stryper T-shirt.

1232
01:27:51.833 --> 01:27:53.425
Oh. that girl...

1233
01:27:54.069 --> 01:27:56.401
She just climbed
into our van.

1234
01:27:56.471 --> 01:27:59.065
threw on your shirt.
She was an idiot.

1235
01:28:00.742 --> 01:28:03.438
You know. I don't
wanna be this girl.

1236
01:28:03.512 --> 01:28:04.843
What girl?

1237
01:28:05.580 --> 01:28:10.313
I don't wanna be the girl
that has to stand here

1238
01:28:10.418 --> 01:28:14.514
and hear about what didn't
happen between you and some idiot.

1239
01:28:14.623 --> 01:28:18.684
You don't. And this is bullshit.
anyway. I didn't cheat on you.

1240
01:28:20.595 --> 01:28:24.031
But you never
called. okay?

1241
01:28:24.132 --> 01:28:25.463
Okay.

1242
01:28:25.534 --> 01:28:28.833
I know I should've called. but
